<TITLE> PSC decides to issue circular on 28th BCS exams </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com) The Public Service Commission Tuesday decided to issue a circular on the 28th BCS examinations, a spokesman said. The PSC chairman's private secretary Monzur Hossain told bdnews24.com that the distribution of application forms would start on March 30. The PSC set May 15 as the deadline for submitting the filled-in forms. The application forms will be available with the designated branches of Sonali Bank. Candidates can turn in their applications to the offices of deputy commissioners, apart from the PSC's five regional offices in as many divisional towns. This is the first circular for BCS exams after the reconstruction of the PSC by appointing a new chairman and members. The circular for 27th BCS exams was issued towards the end of 2005, with oral exams still going on. bdnews24.c
